## Cache Efficiency Rules
1. Never add one-off permissions to global settings — use project-level
2. Never change tools/models mid-session — use subagents instead
3. Don't edit this file mid-session — put updates in messages
4. Static content first, dynamic last (this file is structured for caching)

## ECC (Everything Claude Code) System
Installed: developer profile (v1.9.0) — 28 agents, 65+ rules, 68 commands, 248+ skills, full hook lifecycle.

### Key Commands
`/plan` → spec-first planning · `/learn` → extract reusable patterns · `/verify` → verification loop
`/save-session` → persist context to `~/.claude/sessions/` · `/resume-session` → reload last session
`/code-review` → multi-agent review · `/tdd` → test-driven workflow · `/orchestrate` → multi-agent pipeline
`/checkpoint` → git checkpoint · `/build-fix` → auto-resolve build errors · `/quality-gate` → quality checks
`/harness-audit` → audit ECC setup health · `/instinct-status` → learned patterns inventory

### Hook Lifecycle (auto-runs)
- **SessionStart:** load last session context + detect package manager
- **PreToolUse:** block `--no-verify`, tmux reminder, continuous learning observer, config protection
- **PostToolUse:** PR logging, build analysis, quality gate, auto-format, typecheck, continuous learning
- **Stop:** console.log check, session persistence, pattern evaluation, cost tracking, sound notification
- **PreCompact:** save state before context compaction

### Session Memory
Sessions auto-save to `~/.claude/sessions/`. Learned skills persist in `~/.claude/learned-skills/`.
Use `/save-session` before closing. Use `/resume-session` on next startup.

## Quick Reference
- **ECC Agents:** `~/.claude/AGENTS.md` — 28 specialized agents (architect, reviewers, TDD, security, etc.)
- **Skills index:** `~/.claude/SKILLS-INDEX.md` — searchable skill reference (220+ skills)
- **Cheatsheet:** `~/.claude/CHEATSHEET.md` — commands + workflows + best practices
- **Hooks:** ECC lifecycle hooks (see above) + sound notification on completion

## Situational Guides (On-Demand Skills)
These load on-demand — keeps always-loaded context lean:
- Delegating to subagents → `delegation-templates` skill
- Important decision → `dialectic-review` skill (FOR/AGAINST/Referee)
- Post-bug-fix → `operationalize-fixes` skill
- Starting a feature → `evals-before-specs` skill
- Writing agent instructions → `corrective-framing` skill
- Running batch jobs overnight → `overnight-runner` skill
- AI/SEO optimization → `aaio` skill (robots.txt, JSON-LD, markdown twins)
- AI search visibility → `ai-seo` skill

## Rules
1. Never delete files without asking — archive or rename
2. Git commit frequently with conventional commits
3. Secrets: never hardcode — use env vars or 1Password (`op://`)
4. Ports: check `~/clawd/shared/PORT-REGISTRY.md` before binding
5. Skills: check `~/.claude/SKILLS-INDEX.md` before building from scratch
6. Bug fixes: write reproduction test FIRST, then fix, then operationalize
7. Decisions: use dialectic review for anything expensive to reverse
